          <p>Red giants are evolved stars that have exhausted the hydrogen fuel in their cores and expanded dramatically, becoming 10 to 100 times larger than their original size. Their outer layers cool and glow with a characteristic red-orange hue. Our Sun will become a red giant in about 5 billion years, expanding to engulf the inner planets including possibly Earth.</p>
